Singer Olorunyomi Oloruntimilehin aka Bad Boy Timz has slammed his former label Anonymous Music with N200m lawsuit for alleged libel. Bad Boy Timz posted a 3-page scanned copy displaying the lawsuit he filed against his former record label on his Twitter and Instagram pages on Monday, May 24. The 21-year-old singer also revealed his new record label, “Shock Absorbers Music” while he captioned the post displaying a copy of the rejoinder for the Press Release by Anonymous Music on his Instagram page. The caption reads: “Setting the records straight! @shockabsorbersmusic is a new movement.” Few days ago a video clip of Bad Boy Timz in handcuffs was shared on different social media blogs in Nigeria with headlines stating that the singer was arrested for terminating his contract with Anonymous Music and allegedly defrauding them.